AB  - The proceedings contain 22 papers. The topics discussed include: intra-urban vulnerability gap towards urban resilience in Covid-19 pandemic (case of Surakarta greater urban, Indonesia); analyzing climate change in the coastal zone: the case of Kepulauan Riau, Indonesia; a multicriteria approach to assessing landslide community resilience. case study: Bumiaji sub-district; water carrying capacity determination based on ecosystem services in GKS metropolitan area; Surabaya City Surface temperature distribution based on land cover and vegetation density; determination of marine conservation areas by means of satellite imagery and participatory planning in Bawean Island, Gresik Regency, East Java; analysis DPSIR for the strategic environment assessment in planning development in agropolitan areas and minapolitan areas in East Java; a review of adaptive reuse of urban heritage: relevant lesson from Semarang Old Town, Indonesia; and fractal dimensions analysis of urban agglomeration at road intersections in metropolitan Malang Raya.
