AB  - The proceedings contain 48 papers. The topics discussed include: local knowledge: empirical fact to develop community based disaster risk management concept for community resilience at Mangkang Kulon village, Semarang city; assessing evacuation route against Mount Merapi hazard by using least cost path method in Mriyan-Boyolali, Indonesia; landslide hazard analysis and damage assessment for tourism destination at Candikuning village, Tabanan Regency, Bali, Indonesia; spatial analysis of land subsidence and flood pattern based on DInSAR method in Sentinel Sar imagery and weighting method in geo-hazard parameters combination in north Jakarta region; living in prone flooding area: in coastal areas of Semarang; beyond vulnerability assessment: impact of developments toward local adaptive capacity in Kemijen city village, Semarang city; flood risk analysis in Denpasar city, Bali, Indonesia; the impact of urbanization to forest degradation in metropolitan Semarang: a preliminary study; community-based disaster management: a lesson learned from community emergency response management in Banyumas, Indonesia; sensitive land use planning, Malinao, Albay, Philippines; investigation of potential landsubsidence using GNSS CORS UDIP and DinSAR, Sayung, Demak, Indonesia; modelling multi hazard mapping in Semarang city using GIS-fuzzy method; settlement relocation modeling: reacting to Merapi's eruption incident; and understanding student travel behaviour in Semarang city.
