AB  - The policies, strategies and observation on the role of ecosystems as water suppliers for wetland protection and development are discussed in seminar in Geneva. The measures to protect and restore water-related ecosystems include actions to protect forest regeneration from grazing and pasture control in mountain areas. A joint environmental/agricultural programmes and integrated water monitoring of the health water-related ecosystems are suggested. The seminar viewed the role of EUwater framework directive and habitats directive as important tools for shaping integrated water resources management (IWRM) plans in Europe and in implementing the ecosystem approach to water management.
