AB  - A landslide has been dated to spring of 1933 from tree-ring analysis.  From the 52 sampled trees, seven peak periods of movement were registered within the site before landslide occurrence: 1785, 1815, 1827, 1829, 1852-1853, 1871-1872, 1897 and 1926.  After a slow progression lasting 200 yr, the slope movements accelerated in 1926, as indicated by suppressed growth rings.  It is proposed here that the landslide was the outcome of a long-term slope development partly controlled by climate (precipitation).-from English summary
