TI  - Investigation of Pioneer on Denuded Land (II) On the Tertiary Landslides in the Basin of Arao River
PY  - 1960
T2  - THE JOURNAL OF THE JAPANESE FORESTRY SOCIETY
VL  - 42
IS  - 11
SP  - 395
EP  - 405
UR  - https://www.scopus.com/inward/record.uri?eid=2-s2.0-85007907437&partnerID=40&md5=750dd8fe7c7304c31a2bd1c3c77b22aa
AB  - This paper deals with the pioneer vegetation on the tertiary landslides in the basin of Arao river (Miyagi prefecture). The object of this investigation is to offer the measures to green the denuded land. It was investigated in 10 landslide areas of the same succession to observe the developmental stages of the community and the resultant changes in its composition and structure. The results of synecological studies on the vegetation are briefly summarized as follows: 1. It is recognized that the vegetations in the initial stage are formed of the following two herbs communities, which are different under conditions of ground surface. Surface of talus cone: Artemisia montana-Petasites japonicus var. giganteas-Equisetum arvense comm. Sliding surface: Aruncus sylvester-Salix Reinii-Parnassia palustris comm. After this stage, these vegetations are succeeded progressive forest community of Alnus hirsuta var. sivirica with a few heliotropic shrubs. Subsequently, it is surmised that the progressive community will be succeeded, in the future, by forest one of Fagus crenata or Fagus crenata-Quercus mongolica var. grosseserrata, which is similar to near forest. 2. As regards the life form of spectra in each communities, in the initial stage, the therophytes (Th), the hemicryptophytes (H) and the geophytes (G) show a large majerity percentage on the whole. With the progress of stage, however, the occupancy percentage of these types decrease and that of phanerophytes (MM, M, N, L, Ch) increase gradually. As regards the migrule type of spectra, in the initial stage, the migratory plants (Di~Da) and root-stock plants (Ri~Ra) represent a large majority percentage, but with the progress of stage, its gradual decrease is observed. 3. The initiation of vegetation is started, when the movement of debris on the foot of a rupture surface is stopped and its slope is formed into the talus cone type. After the destructure and development of vegetation are repeated several times, the vegetational cover is spreaded to the upper. The intrusion from the side and upside forest community is remarkable after the progressive stage. 4. As the effects of the vegetational development to rupture surface, with the progress of stage, the horizons in soil profile are differentiated clearly and moreover, the root system and the animal activity in the soil loose the soil and increase the macro-pore on the surface soil. The volume weight, the compaction and the value of pH are decreased, but the amount of humus, the total porosity and some erodibilities are increased. 5. From this investigation, as the good plants for soil coservation in this area, the author found 10 species (Alnus hirsuta var. sivirica etc.) in trees, 5 species (Weigela hortensis etc.) in shrubs, 22 species (Aruncus sylvester etc.) in herbs. © 1960, THE JAPANESE FORESTRY SOCIETY. All rights reserved.
