AB  - Forty-nine landslides aged 1-155 years and surrounding terrain were studied in the Queen Charlotte Islands to elucidate vegetation and soil development and impacts on forest productivity. Because of lower growth rates caused by relatively poor soil conditions and competition by red alder (Alnus rubra Bong.), production of wood on slides to 60 years was estimated at only 30% of that produced in similarly aged logged stands. -from Authors
