AD  - Dept of Geology & Mineralogy, Hokkaido Univ, Japan.
AB  - Numano-hara bog formed c4000 yr BP in a cool and moist climate. The result of pollen analysis suggests the following 3 pollen assemblage zones. During the period of Zone Nu-III (4000-2000 yr BP), Betula ermanii was most dominant. Zone Nu-II (2000-400 yr BP) is characterized by the decrease of B. ermanii and the dominance of Picea glehnii as a result of the expansion of the bog in a cooler and moister climate. Also, a needle-leaved forest composed of P. glehnii and/or P. jezoensis and Abies sacharinensis spread to the lower areas. Finally, the bog decreased in size under a slightly drier condition, and B. ermanii re-invaded at the period of Zone Nu-I (400 yr BP-present). The start of the Midorino-numa bog is a little prior to 1300 yr BP, whereas the Basho-numa bog is considered to have orginated between 1300 and 5000 yr BP. Although B. ermanii invaded into the landslide area in an early stage, P. glahnii increased after the bog formed (Zone Mi-II). At 1300 yr BP the forest around the bog reached the climax P. glehnii forest just like the present one (Zone Mi-I).-from English summary
