AB  - Using a series of photographs and diagrams, efforts at soil regeneration in Taranaki, NZ, are described. Colluvial soils gradually recover in landslip areas to a depth of 20 cm in 90 yr, assisted by a succession of vegetational associations. But the overall soil mantle is decreasing and will inevitably affect land management. -D.A.Lewis
